WEBVTT

00:15.223 --> 00:17.349
I'm impressed you all managed to escape.

00:17.350 --> 00:20.060
- M… Miss All Sunday.
- Who's Miss All Sunday?

00:20.061 --> 00:22.981
She's Baroque Works's second-in-command.
She's vicious.

00:27.861 --> 00:29.571
Don't point those things at me.

00:30.488 --> 00:32.365
It's dangerous.

00:34.325 --> 00:36.286
Whoa!

00:38.913 --> 00:40.372
No need for that.

00:40.373 --> 00:42.709
If I were here to kill you,
you'd already be dead.

00:44.419 --> 00:48.422
Nice to see you again, Miss Wednesday.
Or is it Princess Vivi today?

00:48.423 --> 00:50.924
I was sad to hear of Mr. 8's passing.

00:50.925 --> 00:52.927
Don't you dare talk about Igaram!

00:53.636 --> 00:55.764
No need to get worked up. Hmm.

00:56.264 --> 00:58.766
So you're captain
of the Straw Hat Pirates,

00:58.767 --> 01:01.394
Monkey D. Luffy.

01:03.730 --> 01:08.192
- Hey! Give me back my hat!
- It's quite unfortunate for you.

01:08.193 --> 01:11.445
Your Log Pose has set
to an island called Little Garden.

01:11.446 --> 01:14.656
The dangers there
will likely be your demise.

01:14.657 --> 01:19.079
We can handle anything the Grand Line
throws at us. Now give me back my hat!

01:24.793 --> 01:26.294
I'm here with an offer.

01:28.379 --> 01:30.172
- An Eternal Pose?
- What's that?

01:30.173 --> 01:34.134
An Eternal Pose is a Log Pose that
always points at one particular island.

01:34.135 --> 01:37.596
With this Eternal Pose,
you'll be able to sail to a remote island,

01:37.597 --> 01:41.225
avoiding any trouble you'd undoubtedly
be facing from Little Garden,

01:41.226 --> 01:42.477
or my organization.

01:43.103 --> 01:45.688
If you agree to hide out there,
no one will ever find you.

01:46.272 --> 01:48.023
I can guarantee your safety.

01:48.024 --> 01:49.691
Great! Then it's settled.

01:49.692 --> 01:52.945
- So you're coming with us?
- Keep it in your pants. She's the enemy.

01:52.946 --> 01:54.030
Sounds like a trap.

01:54.614 --> 01:55.698
What do you say?

01:56.908 --> 01:58.076
I won't offer twice.

02:07.335 --> 02:08.503
Luffy, no!

02:12.006 --> 02:14.591
You don't get to decide
where this ship goes.

02:14.592 --> 02:15.802
How tragic.

02:18.638 --> 02:20.806
When you took
the fugitive princess onboard,

02:20.807 --> 02:23.058
you put a target on all your backs.

02:23.059 --> 02:26.186
You may think you're unstoppable…

02:26.187 --> 02:27.981
…Monkey D. Luffy,

02:28.481 --> 02:32.068
but your friends aren't made of rubber.

02:33.736 --> 02:35.738
Good luck.

02:51.212 --> 02:52.380
What just happened?

02:52.881 --> 02:56.508
We just received a mysterious visit
from a beautiful stranger.

02:56.509 --> 02:58.886
You don't understand.
If Miss All Sunday knows where we are,

02:58.887 --> 03:01.723
then it's only a matter of time
before more Baroque Works agents find us.

03:02.307 --> 03:04.308
They won't stop until we're all dead.

03:04.309 --> 03:08.937
Maybe we were a little hasty with
the turning down the run-and-hide plan.

03:08.938 --> 03:11.315
- I don't run and hide.
- That's cool.

03:11.316 --> 03:12.775
But what if I did?

03:16.654 --> 03:17.947
Nah.

03:19.282 --> 03:21.867
Why is he the only one
taking this threat seriously?

03:21.868 --> 03:25.245
- Baroque Works doesn't scare us.
- Zoro just took down a hundred of them.

03:25.246 --> 03:29.124
Officer agents like Mr. 5 and
Miss Valentine are far more formidable.

03:29.125 --> 03:31.251
Many of them have devil fruit powers.

03:31.252 --> 03:33.629
You don't need to worry. I'll protect you.

03:33.630 --> 03:36.215
- Don't lie to the lady.
- I would never lie to a lady.

03:36.216 --> 03:40.220
Luffy, I will forever be grateful
that you got me out of Whisky Peak.

03:40.720 --> 03:41.596
I made a promise.

03:42.180 --> 03:43.556
And you fulfilled it.

03:44.599 --> 03:47.060
But I won't stay
and let them come for the rest of you.

03:47.644 --> 03:50.480
When we get to Little Garden,
I'll find my own way to Alabasta.

04:05.912 --> 04:08.497
Now this is
what we came to the Grand Line for!

04:08.498 --> 04:10.499
I've never seen anything like it.

04:10.500 --> 04:14.878
Why do they call it Little Garden?
It does not seem very little to me.

04:14.879 --> 04:18.090
I don't know, but I am excited to explore.

04:18.091 --> 04:20.384
This island wasn't on
any of the maps I've ever seen,

04:20.385 --> 04:23.470
so if it's uncharted,
it's probably uninhabited.

04:23.471 --> 04:25.515
- Huh?
- Maybe for good reason.

04:26.766 --> 04:29.268
If there's no people,
then there's no boat to take me home.

04:29.269 --> 04:30.727
I guess you're stuck with us.

04:30.728 --> 04:33.731
In the meantime, adventure awaits!

04:34.607 --> 04:35.565
I'm starving.

04:35.566 --> 04:36.692
Well, it's a good thing

04:36.693 --> 04:39.903
that the pirate lunches are packed
and ready for exploring.

04:39.904 --> 04:41.406
Whoo!

04:42.573 --> 04:44.200
All right!

04:45.660 --> 04:48.663
Hello, Little Garden!

04:49.872 --> 04:53.834
We can't wait to see
what you have in store for us!

04:53.835 --> 04:55.628
In store for us!

05:03.636 --> 05:06.638
The island heard me!

05:06.639 --> 05:08.223
It sounds so big.

05:08.224 --> 05:11.060
It sounds like dinner! Mmm!

05:11.602 --> 05:15.314
- I'm gonna go hunt some game.
- How? By kicking it to death?

05:15.315 --> 05:17.317
- You think you could do better?
- Than you?

05:18.234 --> 05:19.443
Easy.

05:19.444 --> 05:22.780
Let's make a bet then, shall we?
Whomever kills dinner wins.

05:26.617 --> 05:27.577
You're on.

05:28.411 --> 05:29.412
Mmm.

05:29.912 --> 05:32.081
- Come on, everyone!
- Vivi.

05:33.333 --> 05:34.334
You coming?

05:37.503 --> 05:38.796
Let's go!

05:40.173 --> 05:41.715
Everybody stick together.

05:41.716 --> 05:44.260
Right. No running off
into the jungle, okay?

05:57.398 --> 05:58.315
This way!

05:58.316 --> 05:59.359
Luffy!

06:02.779 --> 06:05.239
Are we… are we splitting up?

06:06.032 --> 06:08.076
- Are you sure that's a good idea?
- Whoa!

06:08.659 --> 06:09.535
Oh.

06:19.295 --> 06:21.588
Oh.

06:21.589 --> 06:24.174
I've seen plants like these
in books before,

06:24.175 --> 06:27.135
but they're supposed to be extinct.

06:27.136 --> 06:28.513
This one smells pretty good.

06:33.393 --> 06:34.852
This one's hungry.

06:38.064 --> 06:39.107
Whoa.

06:45.822 --> 06:47.448
Well, whatever animal we heard

06:49.033 --> 06:50.492
went this way.

06:50.493 --> 06:51.910
Pretty sure it went that way.

06:51.911 --> 06:54.914
- Are you questioning my hunting skills?
- Skills? Like you have any.

06:57.708 --> 06:58.751
That way.

07:00.753 --> 07:01.920
Don't worry, Vivi.

07:01.921 --> 07:05.007
We'll help you find a way
to get to Alabasta on the next island.

07:06.551 --> 07:08.427
When Luffy turned down
Miss All Sunday's offer,

07:08.428 --> 07:09.970
he put you all in danger.

07:09.971 --> 07:13.765
And you just went along with it. Why?

07:13.766 --> 07:17.645
I know how Luffy may seem,
but he actually…

07:19.230 --> 07:20.898
He's got a lot of…

07:23.609 --> 07:26.279
I actually don't know
how to put it into words, but

07:27.196 --> 07:29.198
when you see it, you see it.

07:34.370 --> 07:35.704
- Ow.
- Mmm.

07:35.705 --> 07:37.456
You gotta try some of these!

07:37.457 --> 07:39.291
Are you trying to kill us?

07:39.292 --> 07:41.502
Get down from there,
and stop acting like an idiot.

07:43.713 --> 07:44.755
Where's Usopp?

07:48.092 --> 07:52.263
He probably went back to the ship.
I will find him. Just, uh,

07:53.097 --> 07:54.557
keep Luffy out of trouble.

07:55.349 --> 07:58.060
I wonder what's this way! Guys, come on!

08:01.772 --> 08:05.943
Ah.

08:08.863 --> 08:09.906
Mmm.

08:10.406 --> 08:12.200
Have you ever seen
something like this before?

08:13.409 --> 08:14.576
You mean a fern?

08:14.577 --> 08:18.039
Yes. Though they're usually not so big.

08:20.416 --> 08:23.710
What about these?
Have you ever seen something like this?

08:23.711 --> 08:26.964
Yes, Luffy. I've seen berries.

08:28.382 --> 08:29.883
Are you sure those are edible?

08:29.884 --> 08:30.885
Mmm.

08:39.644 --> 08:40.645
Whoa.

08:42.063 --> 08:43.773
What about this?

08:45.775 --> 08:47.652
Have you ever seen something like

08:48.444 --> 08:49.362
this?

08:50.738 --> 08:52.156
No, Luffy.

08:53.241 --> 08:56.035
I've definitely never seen
anything like this.

09:00.289 --> 09:03.251
It's a prehistoric island.

09:04.126 --> 09:07.087
Navigating between the islands
in the Grand Line is so difficult

09:07.088 --> 09:12.009
that I bet this has stayed untouched
for thousands of years.

09:13.344 --> 09:14.928
Since the age of the di--

09:14.929 --> 09:16.222
I wanna ride one!

09:22.895 --> 09:24.729
What makes you think it went this way?

09:24.730 --> 09:27.608
I know what I'm doing.
It's around here somewhere.

09:32.113 --> 09:33.614
Admit it. You're lost.

09:34.740 --> 09:36.533
Do you even know what we're looking for?

09:36.534 --> 09:38.326
I mean, judging by these tracks,

09:38.327 --> 09:40.704
I'd say the animal
has pretty sizable claws.

09:40.705 --> 09:42.415
So chicken soup for dinner.

09:44.625 --> 09:45.875
You're definitely lost.

09:45.876 --> 09:47.711
Do you ever shut up, Mosshead?

09:47.712 --> 09:50.630
- Thought we were hunting, not poking dirt.
- Hunting takes patience.

09:50.631 --> 09:54.467
Okay, you don't need to explain to me.
Pirate hunter. Remember?

09:54.468 --> 09:56.971
Yeah, pirates and animals
behave differently.

09:58.055 --> 09:59.014
Most of the time.

09:59.015 --> 10:01.141
When I wanna kill something,
I just go and kill it.

10:01.142 --> 10:03.977
Yeah, well, finesse
is a virtue that you lack.

10:03.978 --> 10:06.688
How much finesse did it take
to get tied up in Whisky Peak?

10:06.689 --> 10:08.398
I was about to escape.

10:08.399 --> 10:10.859
Sure you were.
Why don't you stick to baking cookies?

10:10.860 --> 10:13.361
Baking and cooking are
entirely different culinary disciplines

10:13.362 --> 10:14.447
with distinctive techniques.

10:19.035 --> 10:20.201
Not a chicken.

10:20.202 --> 10:21.412
Definitely not a chicken.

10:32.840 --> 10:35.258
Back already? Why? What happened?

10:35.259 --> 10:36.302
Usopp?

10:37.219 --> 10:38.137
What are you doing?

10:39.221 --> 10:40.597
Just polishing the railings.

10:40.598 --> 10:42.558
Didn't realize they needed polishing.

10:43.643 --> 10:44.644
Yeah, well,

10:46.020 --> 10:47.146
not anymore.

10:49.231 --> 10:52.233
Look, I know you're scared.

10:52.234 --> 10:53.611
I'm not scared.

10:56.030 --> 10:57.281
Just allergic.

10:57.782 --> 11:00.200
To potentially dangerous
and uncharted islands.

11:00.201 --> 11:02.912
Didn't we set out to sea
to have adventures like this?

11:03.621 --> 11:04.705
Well, yeah.

11:05.373 --> 11:08.458
But that Baroque Works lady knows
something about this island we don't.

11:08.459 --> 11:09.502
You heard her.

11:10.378 --> 11:11.461
"Good luck."

11:11.462 --> 11:13.463
She was just trying to scare us!

11:13.464 --> 11:17.218
I mean, look around us. When will we
ever get to see something this incredible?

11:19.512 --> 11:21.263
You're starting to sound like Luffy.

11:23.015 --> 11:24.225
Come on.

11:27.978 --> 11:30.022
- What is that?
- I don't know.

11:30.981 --> 11:32.900
But it can't kill me if I'm already dead.

11:44.495 --> 11:46.956
Do you have any ale? Huh?

11:47.832 --> 11:48.666
Ale?

11:51.335 --> 11:52.461
Huh?

12:06.392 --> 12:09.019
You know what I like after a good drink?

12:09.812 --> 12:10.812
Mm-mmm.

12:10.813 --> 12:12.022
Lunch.

12:13.065 --> 12:16.943
Look out! No! No, no, no!

12:16.944 --> 12:20.071
Whoo!

12:20.072 --> 12:21.322
Luffy!

12:21.323 --> 12:24.033
You should really get down from there.

12:24.034 --> 12:29.205
It may seem docile,
but it is still a dinosaur!

12:29.206 --> 12:30.332
Down?

12:30.833 --> 12:32.542
No. No way!

12:32.543 --> 12:36.629
I've got a view of the whole island
up here. You've got to see!

12:36.630 --> 12:38.591
I really don't!

12:41.886 --> 12:44.637
Luffy! What are you doing?

12:44.638 --> 12:45.848
Aah! Oh!

12:46.891 --> 12:48.058
Oh.

12:48.809 --> 12:51.061
It's okay. I got you.

12:54.815 --> 12:56.192
Pretty good view, huh?

12:58.569 --> 13:00.404
How can you enjoy this?

13:00.988 --> 13:06.785
Baroque Works are hunting us down,
and you're having fun riding a dinosaur.

13:06.786 --> 13:08.370
What do they ride in Arrabiata?

13:11.415 --> 13:14.375
In Alabasta, we ride ducks.

13:14.376 --> 13:15.503
Huh?

13:16.086 --> 13:18.839
My loyal duck companion back home
is named Karoo.

13:19.423 --> 13:20.257
Wow.

13:21.550 --> 13:22.467
Ducks!

13:22.468 --> 13:25.221
I don't think I've ever met a duck
big enough to ride.

13:25.721 --> 13:29.433
Well, actually, I don't think
I've ever met a princess either.

13:30.226 --> 13:31.476
Do you live in a castle?

13:31.477 --> 13:34.521
I live in a palace
in the capital city of Alubarna.

13:34.522 --> 13:37.065
It has secret passageways

13:37.066 --> 13:40.361
and the most beautiful rooftop garden
you've ever seen.

13:40.861 --> 13:43.112
Do you eat lots of fancy food?

13:43.113 --> 13:46.867
The palace chef will make you
whatever you want, any time of day.

13:47.493 --> 13:48.618
Oh!

13:48.619 --> 13:50.870
You can get ice cream sundaes
at three in the morning?

13:50.871 --> 13:51.789
No.

13:52.289 --> 13:53.749
I'm not a child.

13:55.334 --> 13:56.251
Oh.

13:56.252 --> 13:58.587
Um… I'm sorry.

14:00.381 --> 14:01.632
I just need to get home.

14:05.469 --> 14:06.345
You will.

14:22.361 --> 14:23.361
You smell that?

14:23.362 --> 14:24.446
Smell what?

14:25.739 --> 14:26.574
Food.

14:27.074 --> 14:28.033
Dino!

14:28.534 --> 14:29.535
That way!

14:40.254 --> 14:41.213
Okay.

14:42.256 --> 14:45.925
- I guess there's dinosaurs on this island.
- One less now.

14:45.926 --> 14:47.802
Ooh, this thing could feed a village.

14:47.803 --> 14:49.804
I've never cooked a dinosaur before.

14:49.805 --> 14:52.432
I've never killed one before.
Big day for both of us.

14:52.433 --> 14:53.767
You…

14:54.268 --> 14:57.730
you didn't kill anything, okay?
I killed this dinosaur.

14:58.397 --> 15:00.940
You think you killed a Tyrannosaurus Rex
with a kick?

15:00.941 --> 15:03.026
You just saw me do exactly that.

15:03.027 --> 15:04.235
Look here.

15:04.236 --> 15:07.614
This is where my sword, an actual weapon,
sliced through. Do you see that?

15:07.615 --> 15:12.828
A flesh wound, maybe, okay?
But here is where my kick made impact,

15:13.621 --> 15:15.331
actually bringing the beast down.

15:19.168 --> 15:21.628
- You hear that?
- What? The sound of me winning the bet?

15:21.629 --> 15:24.757
I can't wait to see Nami's face
when I make her a T. rex tartare.

16:05.965 --> 16:06.966
Who's there?

16:20.604 --> 16:21.814
We're getting close.

16:23.023 --> 16:23.857
How do you know?

16:24.566 --> 16:26.193
My nose is never wrong.

16:31.907 --> 16:34.493
This is the most beautiful thing
I've ever seen in my life!

16:35.119 --> 16:37.578
Uh… Luffy?

16:37.579 --> 16:40.708
I think that food belongs to someone.

16:43.585 --> 16:46.213
Who dares steal my rations?

16:46.714 --> 16:48.132
Mmm.

16:53.429 --> 16:56.849
Humans don't tend to survive long
on Little Garden.

16:57.433 --> 17:00.101
Yeah, because they get eaten by giants.

17:00.102 --> 17:04.106
Gosh, I am starved.

17:04.606 --> 17:08.109
Nami, I don't want to be stew.

17:08.110 --> 17:10.820
We did not come all of this way
to die in a cave.

17:10.821 --> 17:12.656
We just need to find a way to escape.

17:14.533 --> 17:16.493
It looks like he's some kind of warrior.

17:18.078 --> 17:19.829
Or a butcher.

17:19.830 --> 17:23.416
Listen. I am going to look
for a way to get us out of here.

17:23.417 --> 17:29.380
And you can distract him with one
of Captain Usopp's tales of bravery.

17:29.381 --> 17:30.966
Okay?

17:33.677 --> 17:34.636
A long one.

17:35.512 --> 17:36.597
Right.

17:37.264 --> 17:38.223
Okay.

17:38.807 --> 17:39.974
Yeah.

17:39.975 --> 17:41.602
I am a warrior.

17:42.394 --> 17:43.562
He's a warrior.

17:45.147 --> 17:46.273
I'm a warrior.

17:46.774 --> 17:48.859
It's the same. Same.

17:49.359 --> 17:50.194
We're the same.

17:55.115 --> 17:57.117
You've got a lot of sharp things!

17:57.618 --> 17:59.286
Sorry, what was that?

18:03.999 --> 18:06.335
I said that's an incredible axe you have.

18:07.586 --> 18:14.133
I have wielded lances, spears, hammers.

18:14.134 --> 18:20.390
But the bruiser axe
is my weapon of choice.

18:21.892 --> 18:23.769
It's… beautiful.

18:25.312 --> 18:28.315
Are you interested in weapons?

18:29.316 --> 18:30.859
Oh, yeah.

18:31.944 --> 18:37.533
I once brandished a five-ton hammer
in battle against a mole monster.

18:38.784 --> 18:40.410
Mmm.

18:44.915 --> 18:49.169
Tell me. How did you defeat this beast?

18:49.670 --> 18:50.754
Well, I…

18:52.798 --> 18:56.759
Well, the creature was scared, naturally,
so it fled underground.

18:56.760 --> 18:59.428
But that didn't stop Captain Usopp!

18:59.429 --> 19:02.849
I tore through earth…
…until I caught the creature.

19:02.850 --> 19:04.350
"Come here!"

19:04.351 --> 19:07.396
Boom!

19:10.107 --> 19:11.733
And when the dust settled,

19:12.901 --> 19:15.154
there wasn't a structure left standing.

19:16.321 --> 19:18.198
That's how I got the nickname…

19:20.742 --> 19:24.328
Lord of Destruction!

19:24.329 --> 19:25.788
The Lord of Destruction?

19:25.789 --> 19:29.083
You must be very brave.

19:29.084 --> 19:30.335
And tough.

19:31.587 --> 19:34.380
- Just like my muscles. Stringy.
- Mmm.

19:34.381 --> 19:36.466
Zero flavor, coincidentally.

19:37.050 --> 19:39.385
A warrior of such strength

19:39.386 --> 19:43.724
must have an equally strong appetite.

19:45.767 --> 19:47.186
Stew?

19:50.564 --> 19:51.732
Wait.

19:52.399 --> 19:56.153
You're… not going to eat <i>us</i>?

19:56.778 --> 19:59.697
Is that what you thought?
I wanted to <i>eat</i> you?

19:59.698 --> 20:02.325
- Well, yeah, absolutely.
- Seemed purposeful.

20:02.326 --> 20:05.453
I… I don't eat people!

20:05.454 --> 20:09.999
The only thing
I'm starved for is… is conversation.

20:10.000 --> 20:13.003
That's why I wanted to have you for lunch!

20:18.008 --> 20:19.259
Have

20:20.719 --> 20:22.304
you for lunch.

20:25.057 --> 20:26.766
I hear it now.

20:26.767 --> 20:28.352
My apologies.

20:28.852 --> 20:31.521
Allow me to introduce myself.

20:32.022 --> 20:36.859
I am Brogy the Red Ogre,

20:36.860 --> 20:40.781
Elbaph's strongest warrior!

20:41.865 --> 20:42.866
I'm Nami!

20:43.784 --> 20:49.623
- I'm--
- Captain Usopp, Lord of Destruction!

20:53.043 --> 20:53.919
Yeah.

20:55.796 --> 20:58.840
Pleased to meet you both.

21:08.225 --> 21:10.978
- Hurry up!
- You are welcome to help.

21:20.404 --> 21:21.238
What?

21:22.906 --> 21:24.533
I have this feeling like

21:25.784 --> 21:26.951
someone's watching us.

21:26.952 --> 21:27.952
Don't do that.

21:27.953 --> 21:29.746
Don't get all paranoid on me.

21:30.664 --> 21:34.459
There's no one here but the princess
and those damn Straw Hats.

21:35.210 --> 21:36.544
Just need to kill them before--

21:36.545 --> 21:39.756
Mr. Zero finds out we failed
and sends someone to kill us?

21:44.678 --> 21:48.140
Bing. Bang. Boom.

21:56.356 --> 21:58.567
God, I hate tropical island jobs.

21:59.401 --> 22:01.819
The sun is murder on my porcelain skin.

22:01.820 --> 22:04.323
Yeah, tell me about it.
I'm sweating bullets here.

22:04.823 --> 22:08.994
- You do know you can take your coat off?
- No way. It's part of my look.

22:15.292 --> 22:16.710
Shit.

22:18.545 --> 22:20.005
He sent the psychos.

22:28.305 --> 22:31.808
My, my, aren't you two in trouble?

22:37.981 --> 22:41.609
Should have saved yourself the trip,
Mr. 3. This is our job.

22:41.610 --> 22:44.279
Not anymore. Hmm.

22:45.155 --> 22:46.906
Mr. Zero was quite perturbed

22:46.907 --> 22:49.909
to learn that you let
the princess escape at Whisky Peak

22:49.910 --> 22:55.498
and added a whole pirate crew
to our to-do list.

22:55.499 --> 22:57.376
- We have a plan.
- Please.

22:57.959 --> 22:59.086
Stop speaking.

23:00.712 --> 23:02.630
I've taken over your assignment.

23:02.631 --> 23:05.216
In fact, my partner's
already in the jungle,

23:05.217 --> 23:07.260
putting our plan in motion.

23:08.136 --> 23:09.638
As for you two,

23:10.430 --> 23:11.348
hmm…

23:12.057 --> 23:14.141
I could have some fun with you.

23:14.142 --> 23:18.604
Leave your twisted bodies on the beach
for the Unluckies to finish off.

23:18.605 --> 23:21.024
I don't think Mr. Zero would mind.

23:23.110 --> 23:23.944
Wouldn't try it.

23:25.195 --> 23:26.446
Or…

23:27.614 --> 23:33.411
The pirates have fallen in
with two annoyingly friendly giants

23:33.412 --> 23:35.288
who could make my plan

23:36.373 --> 23:37.707
complicated.

23:38.667 --> 23:41.753
Help me get rid of the giants, and

23:42.295 --> 23:45.674
I'll recommend Mr. Zero not kill you.

23:49.886 --> 23:51.304
At least not for this.

23:54.224 --> 23:55.058
Mmm.

23:55.559 --> 23:56.810
This is amazing!

24:01.440 --> 24:03.942
- Do you wanna try some of mine?
- Mmm.

24:09.781 --> 24:12.741
Hey! I said some!

24:12.742 --> 24:15.537
Very tiny, but very tasty.

24:17.998 --> 24:19.748
I don't even know what it was.

24:19.749 --> 24:23.586
It's called beef bourguignon.
One of our chef's specialties.

24:23.587 --> 24:25.005
Compliments to your chef.

24:27.340 --> 24:29.049
Hold up. Are you a pirate?

24:29.050 --> 24:32.345
Indeed.
Captain of the Giant Warrior Pirates.

24:34.222 --> 24:37.142
We both love meat,
and we're both pirate captains?

24:38.393 --> 24:39.728
What are the chances?

24:42.564 --> 24:46.317
I'm Monkey D. Luffy,
and I'm gonna be King of the Pirates.

24:46.318 --> 24:48.403
I didn't know pirates had a king.

24:49.321 --> 24:53.365
Then again, I have been on this island
for a very long time.

24:53.366 --> 24:54.534
I am Dorry,

24:55.035 --> 24:56.368
the Blue Ogre.

24:56.369 --> 24:58.246
Elbaph's strongest warrior.

24:58.830 --> 25:00.873
This is Vivi. She's a princess.

25:00.874 --> 25:01.790
Luffy.

25:01.791 --> 25:03.250
Your Highness.

25:03.251 --> 25:04.710
Should I bow?

25:04.711 --> 25:06.128
No. No, no, no.

25:06.129 --> 25:07.130
And please,

25:07.714 --> 25:09.006
it's just Vivi.

25:09.007 --> 25:11.801
Charmed to make your acquaintance,
Just Vivi.

25:12.385 --> 25:14.554
She's on her way home to save her kingdom.

25:15.764 --> 25:18.391
I'm trying.

25:19.142 --> 25:23.688
But… I don't know
if I'll make it in time, and

25:24.189 --> 25:25.398
without Igaram…

25:25.899 --> 25:27.526
Who's Igaram?

25:28.902 --> 25:30.070
My friend.

25:31.571 --> 25:33.698
He died protecting me.

25:34.491 --> 25:37.452
It sounds like this friend is a hero.

25:38.078 --> 25:39.453
He died with honor.

25:39.454 --> 25:41.413
It doesn't matter how he died.

25:41.414 --> 25:44.042
He's gone,
and I couldn't do anything to stop it.

25:45.335 --> 25:47.754
In Elbaph, we have a ritual.

25:48.505 --> 25:50.297
When a warrior dies,

25:50.298 --> 25:52.800
we place their body upon a pyre
and burn it

25:52.801 --> 25:55.762
so their souls can rise to the heavens.

25:56.263 --> 25:59.558
Perhaps you would like to do the same
for your friend.

26:00.308 --> 26:02.686
I don't even have his body.

26:04.771 --> 26:05.605
Hey.

26:06.898 --> 26:08.024
What about this?

26:38.680 --> 26:39.639
Igaram,

26:40.557 --> 26:44.644
your unwavering loyalty to your homeland
will never be forgotten.

26:46.271 --> 26:47.856
But more than that,

26:48.440 --> 26:49.899
you were my support.

26:51.234 --> 26:53.737
You always believed in me,

26:54.237 --> 26:56.740
even when I doubted myself.

26:58.533 --> 27:02.704
You were like a second father to me,
ever since I was little.

27:04.080 --> 27:06.498
And as I traveled far from home,

27:06.499 --> 27:09.460
far from my own father,

27:09.461 --> 27:12.672
you felt like home.

27:14.674 --> 27:16.009
So I thank you.

27:16.593 --> 27:18.553
Not just for your service,

27:19.262 --> 27:20.679
but for your love

27:20.680 --> 27:22.265
and your protection.

27:23.767 --> 27:27.020
I owe you my life.

27:41.534 --> 27:42.702
He was a great man.

27:50.627 --> 27:51.670
Sorry.

27:52.754 --> 27:54.923
It's just beautiful.

28:07.644 --> 28:09.354
The stew was delicious, Brogy.

28:10.105 --> 28:11.355
Thank you.

28:11.356 --> 28:15.025
I just wish I had some <i>semla</i>
to offer you for dessert.

28:15.026 --> 28:16.777
What's <i>semla</i>?

28:16.778 --> 28:20.823
Oh, a spiced sweet bun from Elbaph.

28:20.824 --> 28:26.286
We would feast on great bowls of <i>semla</i>
before the winter solstice festival,

28:26.287 --> 28:28.914
which pays gratitude to the sun god.

28:28.915 --> 28:33.419
One year, I ate a whole table full.

28:33.420 --> 28:35.004
Sounds like someone else I know.

28:35.588 --> 28:37.965
Is everyone in Elbaph a giant like you?

28:37.966 --> 28:41.677
Well, to us, we seem pretty normal.

28:41.678 --> 28:44.680
Why, when I first went overseas,

28:44.681 --> 28:48.768
I was quite surprised
to find everybody else was so small.

28:49.811 --> 28:51.603
What's Elbaph like?

28:51.604 --> 28:52.856
Oh.

28:53.356 --> 28:55.774
It's a beautiful island

28:55.775 --> 29:02.073
with steep mountains
and a massive tree at its center.

29:02.574 --> 29:07.454
And brave warriors
famed for their honor and strength.

29:09.080 --> 29:10.414
I think I'd like it there.

29:10.415 --> 29:12.583
You would.

29:12.584 --> 29:18.464
Even in death, our warriors live on
through tales of their bravery,

29:18.465 --> 29:21.092
much like your own, Captain Usopp.

29:21.593 --> 29:28.266
And a heroic death in battle
is the ultimate expression of courage.

29:32.353 --> 29:35.356
How do you face death without fear?

29:38.777 --> 29:39.861
What was that?

29:40.361 --> 29:42.905
Oh, that's just the volcano.

29:42.906 --> 29:45.282
A volcano? Are we in danger?!

29:45.283 --> 29:48.076
Oh, no, no, not at all.

29:48.077 --> 29:51.539
Well, time to go fight to the death.

29:53.875 --> 29:58.213
In Elbaph, if combat commences
and neither side yields,

29:58.713 --> 30:01.757
judgment is handed down by the gods,

30:01.758 --> 30:04.051
and whoever they deem righteous

30:04.052 --> 30:07.721
will be granted survival
and divine protection.

30:07.722 --> 30:10.349
There is another giant on this island

30:10.350 --> 30:14.061
with whom I share
a long-standing conflict.

30:14.062 --> 30:17.064
So every day, when the volcano erupts,

30:17.065 --> 30:19.192
we engage in a battle to the death.

30:19.901 --> 30:25.280
73,466 duels.

30:25.281 --> 30:29.952
And every day,
those battles have resulted in a draw.

30:29.953 --> 30:31.537
That's a lot of fighting.

30:31.538 --> 30:35.917
Dorry and I have been dueling
for over a hundred years!

30:36.709 --> 30:38.628
A hundred years?

30:39.295 --> 30:40.629
How old are you?

30:40.630 --> 30:44.299
We giants live for 300 years.

30:44.300 --> 30:46.511
And you've been fighting for a hundred?

30:47.136 --> 30:48.137
Over what?

30:50.974 --> 30:55.310
At this point, I don't even remember!

30:55.311 --> 30:57.271
You can't even remember?

30:57.272 --> 30:58.772
How much do you hate each other

30:58.773 --> 31:01.526
that you would fight
for an entire century over nothing?

31:03.653 --> 31:05.238
It's not about hatred.

31:05.780 --> 31:07.490
It's about honor

31:07.991 --> 31:09.241
and conviction!

31:09.242 --> 31:11.827
Right you are, Captain Usopp.

31:11.828 --> 31:14.454
We may not remember why we duel,

31:14.455 --> 31:16.999
but there must be a champion.

31:17.000 --> 31:21.169
In Elbaph, honor comes both from victory

31:21.170 --> 31:24.132
and dying a warrior's death.

31:31.681 --> 31:32.807
Come on!

31:35.810 --> 31:39.938
Do you seriously
want to see two giants duel to the death?

31:39.939 --> 31:42.233
That doesn't sound safe or sane.

31:43.359 --> 31:46.446
Didn't we set out to sea
to have adventures like this?

31:47.739 --> 31:50.741
Yes, we did! Yes, we did!

31:50.742 --> 31:51.826
Whoo!

32:01.294 --> 32:02.253
Huh?

32:15.892 --> 32:16.935
Hmm.

32:29.364 --> 32:30.323
There you are.

32:30.823 --> 32:32.241
What the hell are you doing?

32:34.535 --> 32:37.997
Training. The pomegranate
is the most formidable opponent.

32:38.539 --> 32:43.336
Well, while you were making a fruit salad,
I carved up the entire T. rex by myself.

32:43.920 --> 32:46.297
The femur was so big
it almost broke my boning knife.

32:48.132 --> 32:49.591
Boning knife?

32:49.592 --> 32:51.803
Are you literally, like, five years old?

32:55.264 --> 32:56.599
Hey, what's your problem?

32:59.435 --> 33:00.602
I don't know.

33:00.603 --> 33:02.271
It's like I can't stop…

33:02.939 --> 33:04.815
stop laughing.

33:04.816 --> 33:05.942
Right.

33:07.110 --> 33:12.197
Okay, well, I'm just gonna take the meat
that I killed back to the Merry by myself,

33:12.198 --> 33:14.575
and you can stay here
and keep acting like an idiot.

33:17.912 --> 33:18.954
No, wait. Stop!

33:18.955 --> 33:20.248
Whatever, man.

33:21.791 --> 33:23.084
Boning knife.

33:42.395 --> 33:45.189
A duel between giants?
Can you believe we get to see this?

33:45.732 --> 33:46.732
It's fine.

33:46.733 --> 33:49.569
It's gonna be epic! Whoo!

33:50.611 --> 33:51.612
Huh.

33:52.447 --> 33:53.281
What?

33:53.990 --> 33:55.992
That's why they call it Little Garden.

33:57.118 --> 33:58.786
Because it's little to them.

34:09.464 --> 34:10.965
Good luck with your duel!

34:11.466 --> 34:15.343
I don't need luck, my small friend.
Just the favor of the gods.

34:15.344 --> 34:17.012
Nami! Usopp!

34:17.013 --> 34:19.347
Ah! More tiny folk! Hello!

34:19.348 --> 34:23.644
- Hello, other giant!
- What are you guys doing here?

34:24.145 --> 34:26.271
We met a giant too.
Isn't this place great?

34:26.272 --> 34:27.939
- I know! I was just telling Nami.
- Right!

34:27.940 --> 34:30.526
Giants! Giants!

34:31.569 --> 34:33.279
- Dorry!
- Brogy!

34:34.614 --> 34:36.365
These giants don't hate each other.

34:36.866 --> 34:37.992
They're friends.

34:38.618 --> 34:40.243
Nami, you'll be the voice of reason.

34:40.244 --> 34:42.788
Are we really going to watch
these two giants kill each other?

34:42.789 --> 34:45.166
I think everything's gonna turn out fine.

35:02.683 --> 35:03.893
Is it in there?

35:05.436 --> 35:06.479
Yep.

35:07.355 --> 35:08.314
Let's party.

35:15.113 --> 35:19.658
Today, we stand on the precipice of glory,

35:19.659 --> 35:22.202
where valor meets destiny.

35:22.203 --> 35:25.705
Let this ale fuel the fire in our hearts

35:25.706 --> 35:28.834
as we forge into the embrace of battle!

35:28.835 --> 35:29.836
<i>Skål!</i>

35:32.880 --> 35:34.590
This rock is soft.

35:35.550 --> 35:36.675
Ah.

35:36.676 --> 35:39.553
To the honor we defend,

35:39.554 --> 35:41.263
the glory we seek,

35:41.264 --> 35:44.267
and the camaraderie of true warriors.

35:44.851 --> 35:48.520
May the sun god, Nika, smile down
with pleasure at what he witnesses

35:48.521 --> 35:52.440
and grant us a place
in the great hall of heroes.

35:52.441 --> 35:54.443
<i>- Skål!
- Skål!</i>

36:00.825 --> 36:01.784
Ah.

36:19.468 --> 36:21.387
Aah!

36:43.910 --> 36:45.202
Yes! Boom, boom!

36:45.203 --> 36:47.204
Let's go, Brogy!

36:47.205 --> 36:49.539
Let's go, Dorry!

36:49.540 --> 36:53.336
You're the strongest warrior in Elbaph!

36:54.128 --> 36:55.087
Hey!

37:12.521 --> 37:13.688
Dorry! Dorry! Dorry!

37:13.689 --> 37:17.109
Get him! Let's go! Put him in a stew!

37:18.569 --> 37:19.904
They're so strong!

37:24.116 --> 37:26.993
- Yeah, Dorry, get him!
- Take him down, Brogy!

37:26.994 --> 37:28.870
Dorry! Yeah!

37:28.871 --> 37:31.874
This is legendary. Can you believe
I almost stayed on the boat?

37:32.500 --> 37:33.541
Yeah.

37:33.542 --> 37:36.170
I feel so inspired.

37:37.505 --> 37:39.381
I want to be just like them.

37:39.382 --> 37:41.467
- You want to be a giant?
- No, uh…

37:41.968 --> 37:44.762
But this is what I mean
when I say "brave warrior of the sea."

37:45.263 --> 37:46.472
I want to live

37:47.139 --> 37:49.767
proud and fearless, like Brogy and Dorry.

37:51.018 --> 37:54.063
If Elbaph is an island
full of warriors like these two,

37:54.689 --> 37:56.274
I want to go there someday.

37:56.941 --> 37:57.900
Me too.

37:58.693 --> 37:59.860
I promise we'll go there.

38:01.445 --> 38:02.446
Together.

38:03.197 --> 38:05.156
Whoo!

38:05.157 --> 38:07.158
Yeah!

38:07.159 --> 38:09.704
Those clouds look like a cat.

38:11.163 --> 38:12.999
Nami? Are you feeling all right?

38:13.666 --> 38:15.751
I'd be better if I could pet that cat.

38:17.295 --> 38:18.713
Neither one is giving up!

38:19.297 --> 38:21.465
No wonder it's been going on for so long.

38:25.219 --> 38:26.511
- Whoo!
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

38:26.512 --> 38:27.430
- Whoa!
- Yeah!

38:29.890 --> 38:31.141
- Brogy!
- Dorry!

38:31.142 --> 38:32.475
Why isn't it working?

38:32.476 --> 38:33.728
Just give it a beat.

38:34.395 --> 38:38.816
My Earwax Fancy Cannon will activate
as soon as it fully dissolves.

38:40.526 --> 38:42.027
- I put earwax in his beer.
- I got it.

38:42.028 --> 38:43.154
Oh, okay. Just making sure.

38:51.078 --> 38:51.954
Boom.

38:54.623 --> 38:55.958
Something's wrong with Brogy.

39:00.963 --> 39:04.342
Look! There's smoke coming out of his mug.

39:06.260 --> 39:08.386
But Dorry gave him that beer.

39:08.387 --> 39:11.348
I hate to say it,
but maybe Dorry drugged him.

39:11.349 --> 39:13.808
What? No way.

39:13.809 --> 39:17.395
Brogy and Dorry fight with integrity.
They would never poison each other.

39:17.396 --> 39:21.025
That's right. No one on this island
would ever do such a thing!

39:21.859 --> 39:23.861
Unless we're not the only ones
on the island.

39:27.615 --> 39:28.824
Baroque Works.

39:31.077 --> 39:32.661
Booger guy!

39:33.412 --> 39:35.998
It was you and your booger bombs!

39:38.459 --> 39:40.044
Wait! Luffy, wait!

39:40.544 --> 39:41.628
Stop!

39:41.629 --> 39:43.713
Stop the fight!

39:43.714 --> 39:46.509
This isn't a fair fight.
Something's wrong with Brogy!

39:49.845 --> 39:50.805
Brogy.

39:51.764 --> 39:52.848
Brogy!

39:56.977 --> 39:58.062
No.

40:10.366 --> 40:12.326
No!

40:21.836 --> 40:23.670
By the sword's edge,

40:23.671 --> 40:26.632
I claim my victory in blood!

40:28.634 --> 40:30.136
After a century,

40:30.719 --> 40:33.680
this fight is over.

40:33.681 --> 40:34.765
Hmm.

40:35.766 --> 40:37.518
All according to plan.

40:43.399 --> 40:45.608
Hey, I know you.

40:45.609 --> 40:47.319
I'm hard to forget.

40:53.534 --> 40:54.702
Nami?

40:58.497 --> 40:59.498
Bye, Usopp.

41:02.293 --> 41:03.210
Toodles.

41:20.978 --> 41:22.354
Nami!

41:25.149 --> 41:26.150
Brogy!

41:28.777 --> 41:30.946
No! No! Brogy!

41:33.324 --> 41:35.408
Brogy. No.

41:35.409 --> 41:37.453
This is the judgment of the gods.

41:38.329 --> 41:40.372
Brogy has died a noble death.

41:42.541 --> 41:43.459
No.

41:44.793 --> 41:46.962
No! Didn't you see?

41:47.630 --> 41:49.130
It wasn't a fair fight!

41:49.131 --> 41:52.425
This Baroque Works guy
put a bomb in his ale.

41:52.426 --> 41:54.260
It exploded in his stomach!

41:54.261 --> 41:56.513
The ale that I gave to him?

41:56.514 --> 41:58.474
I tried to stop the fight.

41:59.850 --> 42:02.143
But Brogy went through with it anyway!

42:02.144 --> 42:03.562
I had no idea.

42:05.105 --> 42:06.732
How did I fail to notice?

42:07.316 --> 42:09.068
My dear friend is dead.

42:09.735 --> 42:10.694
For what?

42:11.237 --> 42:12.487
Not honor.

42:12.488 --> 42:13.948
For nothing!

42:15.533 --> 42:19.327
Wait! The people who took
my friend, Nami, they're still out there!

42:19.328 --> 42:20.287
I need your help!

42:22.039 --> 42:23.541
I can't do this alone.

42:29.380 --> 42:31.382
I'll always remember you, Brogy.

42:37.096 --> 42:39.390
Elbaph's strongest warrior.

42:42.977 --> 42:44.562
I couldn't save you.

42:48.315 --> 42:50.109
But I can still save Nami.

43:15.634 --> 43:16.635
Hey.

43:18.804 --> 43:19.638
Who are you?

43:20.889 --> 43:22.308
I was waiting for someone.

43:23.309 --> 43:25.311
But now I'm all lost and alone.

43:27.396 --> 43:28.522
Maybe I can help.

43:31.150 --> 43:32.651
Who are you waiting for?

43:36.488 --> 43:37.489
Luffy!

43:40.701 --> 43:41.618
Luffy.

43:41.619 --> 43:42.786
Get away from her!

43:54.006 --> 43:55.007
Run!

44:02.389 --> 44:04.683
What's the point?

44:05.267 --> 44:06.226
Tag.

44:06.727 --> 44:07.853
You're it.

44:11.482 --> 44:12.691
Nami!

44:14.234 --> 44:15.611
Nami!

44:16.779 --> 44:18.072
Nami, where are you?

44:24.953 --> 44:25.954
Whoa!

44:41.762 --> 44:42.930
Nami?

44:48.477 --> 44:49.645
Anyone?

45:10.624 --> 45:12.000
What up, Miss Wednesday?

45:19.633 --> 45:20.801
My dear friend,

45:21.802 --> 45:24.179
now your home will be empty forevermore.

45:44.658 --> 45:49.329
73,466 draws.

45:51.290 --> 45:52.291
One…

45:55.794 --> 45:57.546
I don't care how you died.

45:58.297 --> 46:02.968
You fought like a proud warrior,
and I will give you a warrior's funeral.

46:10.017 --> 46:11.185
But first,

46:12.227 --> 46:14.479
I will find the people who did this to you

46:14.480 --> 46:16.607
and make them pay.

46:25.157 --> 46:26.492
Such anguish.

46:27.159 --> 46:29.620
Such beautiful suffering.

46:30.704 --> 46:33.165
What is this?

46:33.749 --> 46:35.000
Candle wax.

46:35.501 --> 46:42.299
The Wax Wax fruit gifted me the ability
to produce and manipulate it.

46:44.760 --> 46:46.636
Struggle all you want,

46:46.637 --> 46:51.225
but once it hardens,
the wax is stronger than steel.

46:51.809 --> 46:54.644
Why are you doing this? What do you want?!

46:54.645 --> 46:58.064
I know it doesn't seem fair, but trust me,

46:58.065 --> 47:01.150
there is purpose in your suffering.

47:01.151 --> 47:02.110
You see,

47:03.612 --> 47:05.154
I am an artiste,

47:05.155 --> 47:09.201
and you, my poor, doomed giant friend,

47:09.785 --> 47:13.497
will be my next work of art.

47:41.817 --> 47:42.776
Oh no.
